-- Ukraine’s Turboatom Signs $100 Million Deal With Russian Plant
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2011-12-21T16:03:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/ukraine-s-turboatom-signs-100-million-deal-with-russian-plant.html
VAT Turboatom (TATM) , Ukraine’s biggest
turbine maker, won a $100 million contract to supply turbine and
other equipment to the Rostovskaya nuclear power station in
 Russia .  The equipment is to be supplied by March 2015, the Kharkiv-
based company said in an e-mailed statement today. It is the
biggest contract Turboatom has had in 25 years, the company said
in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
